==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[#Old French|quintal]]'', from mediaeval Latin ''[[quintale]]'', from Arabic {{ARchar|[[قنطار]]}} (qinṭār), ultimately from Latin ''[[centenarius]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈkwɪntəl/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{archaic}} A measure of weight originally equal to a hundred [[pounds]]; later, a [[hundredweight]].
# One hundred [[kilograms]].

